{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6dce22d6-728b-41c7-89ee-4a8e1b001c89","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively supports MTP**. You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs; .NET 10 detects MTP-based test projects automatically.\n\nYou can simply remove line 6:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NjBTreJ4zTmUzLrckD2MuF","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-914cac95e2204a0281e7576b8bffffe9/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-914cac95e2204a0281e7576b8bffffe9/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"2df8f4d6-0306-41af-a858-7fc90ac425d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, the `dotnet test` command uses MTP by default when it detects that the test project is an MTP-based project (i.e., has `EnableMSTestRunner` or uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`).\n\n\nSo with .NET 10, `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is redundant and can be removed from the csproj, while `EnableMSTestRunner` should remain since it's what makes the test project build as an executable using MTP. I should verify this works by checking if dotnet can restore and build the project.","outputTokens":528,"requestId":"67D2:228EC1:2AFBAA3:2F5329B:69FD3626"},"id":"26da41fa-14c6-4c66-8f32-5a88f46a2d01","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:40.711Z","parentId":"7fb6e609-151b-478f-a68c-5eb9bd2101a5"}
